opennlp.ccg.parse
Class Chart

java.lang.Object
  opennlp.ccg.parse.Chart

public class Chart
extends Object

An implementation of the table (or chart) used for chart parsers like CKY. Special functions are provided for combining cells of the chart into another cell. Time or edge or cell limits can be placed on initial chart construction. A pruning value applies to unpacking, which also limits the number of equivalent edges kept during chart construction.

lazyUnpack

public List<Edge> lazyUnpack(int x,
                             int y)
Lazily unpacks the edges in the given cell as an n-best list using a variant of "cube pruning". The algorithm essentially follows Algorithm 2 of Huang and Chiang (2005), with checking for spurious ambiguity.
